This paper is about non-autoregressive neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture based on connectionist temporal classification, which is a technique commonly used in speech recognition, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The authors also mention using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in their experiments, which is a subfield of computer vision (CV), making cs.CV another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimizing the performance of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
